This paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The paper also discusses strategies for achieving the capacity of the network, which could fall under the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of coding techniques, which could be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of quantization, which could be relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
